Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Chop into 2cm sized chunks. Trim the @courgette{1} then halve lengthways.
Thinly slice widthways. Pop the pepper and courgette onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle
with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, scatter over the @ground cumin{1%tsp} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then arrange in a single layer. Roast until
golden brown and soft, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.
Roughly chop the @dill{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Crumble the
@feta cheese{75%g}. Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%can} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} over medium high heat. Once hot,
add the @diced chicken thigh{210%g} and stir fry until golden brown all over,
~{5-6%minutes}. Add the onion and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir
through the @harissa paste{50%g} and cook for a further ~{1%minute}.

Add the lentils, @vegetable stock powder{1%tsp} and @water{75%ml}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} and stir together. Simmer until everything is piping hot
and the chicken is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, squeeze the lemon juice into a #small bowl{} and add the dill and
@olive oil{2%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir together.

Once the veg have roasted, add to the lentils along with a pinch of lemon zest.
Stir together to combine. Add a splash more water if it is dry.

Divide the jumble between plates, scatter over the feta and drizzle over the
lemony dill dressing. Sprinkle over any remaining lemon zest. Enjoy!